verbose_text: Women with diabetes had the highest ferritin measurements compared with women with hGDM and unaffected women (135.1 vs. 59.4 and 62.7 ng/ml, respectively; P < 0.0001), the highest leukocyte counts (8.4 vs. 8.0 and 7.2 cells/ml, respectively; P < 0.0001), and the highest CRP levels (0.88 vs. 0.51 and 0.40 mg/l, respectively; P = 0.0012).
